Key Responsibilities: Design, develop, and maintain backend services using Python. Build and optimize RESTful APIs for application integration
and data exchange. Work with relational and/or NoSQL databases for query development and data modeling. Ensure API performance, scalability,
and security using best practices. Collaborate with frontend, DevOps, and QA teams to deliver end-to-end features. Write reusable, testable, and
maintainable code following clean coding principles. Troubleshoot issues, perform debugging, and support production deployments. Integrate
third-party APIs and external services as required. Maintain documentation and participate in code reviews.

Required Qualifications: 5+ years of hands-on experience in Python backend development. Strong experience in REST API development using
frameworks like Flask, FastAPI, or Django. Working knowledge of SQL databases (MySQL, PostgreSQL) or NoSQL stores. Experience with Git,
API versioning, and CI/CD pipelines. Understanding of authentication standards such as OAuth2, JWT, etc. Strong debugging, problem-solving,
and analytical skills. Preferred Skills: Experience with Docker, containerization, or cloud platforms (AWS/Azure/GCP). Knowledge of message
queues (Kafka, RabbitMQ). Familiarity with microservices architecture. Exposure to API documentation tools (Swagger/OpenAPI).
